headline: Assessing Qualcomm (QCOM) Valuation as New AI Platforms and Strategic Acquisitions Reshape Growth Prospects
summary: Qualcomm (QCOM) just doubled down on AI infrastructure by rolling out new AI200 and AI250 data center platforms and moving to acquire Alphawave IP Group and Arduino, a combination that reshapes its role across cloud and edge AI. See our latest analysis for QUALCOMM. Despite the splashy AI moves, QUALCOMM’s share price is around $170.7 and its recent 30 day share price return of about negative 5.5 percent contrasts with a solid 3 year total shareholder return above 50 percent.
